Legendary British supermodel and philanthropist 
@naomi tells us about her longtime friend @prince and what celebrating his life—four years after we lost his light—means to her, backstage at "Let's Go Crazy: #GRAMMYSalutePrince”. 🎵

A 40,000 square foot warehouse in southeast #LosAngeles has been hosting concerts throughout the coronavirus pandemic. Yet there are only a dozen people working the venue—all of whom are operating at a distance with masks—and while the band is performing at full energy, there's no audience.

@SocialSanctuary has produced approximately 60 events since April, bringing bands, DJs and even comedians into a highly controlled space to record "safe at home" shows for streaming on social media. Their goal is to exceed the traditional in-home production many music fans have become used to while viewing #livestreams during the pandemic, and provide an outlet for professionals whose industry has been decimated by the coronavirus.

Tap the link in our bio to learn more on how Social Sanctuary reimagined live entertainment for the #COVID19 era.

